failure.message: Search Results > History > Original Answer Displayed expected [Based on the information provided in the context, it is stated that Aretec has seven years of experience in support of the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission’s (SEC’s) analytic requirements. It is mentioned that Aretec has worked as a Subject Manager Expert/Quantitative Analyst for the SEC from September 2014 to April 2016. Aretec's experience includes consulting on statistical models to identify anomalies in High Frequency Trading and combat Money Laundering, conducting status meetings with stakeholders and development teams, gathering and validating requirements for IT infrastructure and custom software solutions, and working as a liaison between business owners, stakeholders, developers, and end-users at the SEC. Therefore, based on this information, it can be inferred that Aretec has experience working for the Securities and Exchange Commission.] but found [Based on the context provided, there is no information indicating whether Aretec has knowledge of how to change transmission fluid in a 1965 Shelby Cobra.]
